explanation: This solution uses a stack to keep track of the characters in the lexicographically smallest subsequence. It iterates over the string, and for each character, it pops characters from the stack that are greater than the current character and are not yet in the subsequence. This ensures that the subsequence is lexicographically smallest and contains all distinct characters exactly once.

